		<p>As it says <a href="#contact-me">above</a>, &#8220;Please do not post bug reports or requests for support as comments below (feature requests are fine, though!). If you need help using the add-on, please <a href="mailto:jik+sendlater3@kamens.us">e-mail me</a> instead and I will respond as soon as I can (which is usually very quickly). Thanks!&#8221;</p>
<p>Having said that, it sounds like Send Later thinks Thunderbird is in offline mode. <a href="https://support.mozillamessaging.com/en-US/kb/send-later-instead-of-send-button">This page</a> may help. If Thunderbird puts itself into offline mode after you start composing a message, the button in the compose window will say &#8220;Send&#8221; but it&#8217;ll do&#8221;Send Later&#8221; when you click it.</p>
<p>If that doesn&#8217;t solve your problem, feel free to <a href="mailto:jik+sendlater3@kamens.us">email me</a> and I&#8217;ll troubleshoot further with you.</p>

