			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/02ee400c45c070d8044f80af6838729f?s=32&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D32&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://stuff.mit.edu/~jik/' rel='external' class='url'>jik</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://blog.kamens.us/send-later/comment-page-2/#comment-194852">
			October 30, 2012 at 11:07 am</a>		</div>

		<p>*sigh* You&#8217;re right, it turns out that saving a draft while in offline mode won&#8217;t work, because of a bug in Thunderbird: <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=805626">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=805626</a>.</p>
<p>So you can either use Alt-O to save in Outbox, or another option would be to modify your account settings so that drafts are stored in Local Folders instead of on the IMAP server. Messages stored in a local folder won&#8217;t run afoul of bug 805626.</p>

		<div class="reply">
			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/send-later/?replytocom=194852#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-194852", "194852", "respond", "1637")'>Reply</a>		</div>
